.. _craft_parts_<plugin-key>_plugin:

<BuildSystem> plugin
====================

<BuildSystem> plugin is a plugin that simplifies building projects that use the
<BuildSystem> build system.

Keys
----

This plugin provides the following unique keys.


<prefix>-task
~~~~~~~~~~~~~

**Type:** string

Task to execute with <BuildSystem>.


<prefix>-parameters
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

**Type:** list of strings

Additional command-line arguments passed to the <BuildSystem> command.


<prefix>-use-wrapper
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

**Type:** boolean

Whether to use a project-provided wrapper script.


<prefix>-version
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

**Type:** string

Tool version to bootstrap from official releases when wrapper mode is disabled.


Dependencies
------------

The plugin does not make a runtime available in the target environment. This must be
handled by the developer when defining the part, according to each application's
runtime requirements.


Example
-------

This example shows how to build a real project with the {{plugin_human_name}} plugin.
The following `parts.yaml` demonstrates this plugin:

.. code-block:: yaml

    # Replace with the example from
    # examples/.local-tests/<plugin-key>/parts.yaml
    parts:
      <plugin-key>-example:
        plugin: <plugin-key>
        source: https://example.invalid/project.git
